abstract: Making a case for the nomination, onstage together for one last time in 2019.
snippet: Making a case for the nomination, onstage together for one last time in 2019.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Elizabeth Warren argued that Democrats would defeat President Trump if they “draw the sharpest distinction” with what she called the administration’s corruption — and suggested that Mayor Pete Buttigieg’s high-dollar fund-raising would undermine their ability to do that. Mr. Buttigieg said his party could scarcely afford to hew to such “purity tests” in a race against Mr. Trump.

abstract: Mr. Bloomberg’s proposal, which would offer a government alternative to private health insurance, is similar to plans from some of his more moderate rivals in the 2020 race.
snippet: Mr. Bloomberg’s proposal, which would offer a government alternative to private health insurance, is similar to plans from some of his more moderate rivals in the 2020 race.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Former Mayor Michael R. Bloomberg of New York unveiled a health policy proposal on Thursday that would create a government-run health insurance plan but not provide universal guaranteed coverage, aligning himself with the more moderate wing of the Democratic Party in the 2020 presidential primary.

abstract: Everything you need to know about the 2020 Democratic presidential debate in Los Angeles.
snippet: Everything you need to know about the 2020 Democratic presidential debate in Los Angeles.
lead_paragraph: Only seven Democratic presidential candidates — the fewest yet — will take the stage at Loyola Marymount University on Thursday night, with 46 days to go until the first votes are cast in the Iowa caucuses. Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. remains the leading candidate in national polls, but three candidates are within striking distance, particularly in Iowa: Mayor Pete Buttigieg of South Bend, Ind., Senator Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts and Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont.

abstract: The candidates must know the quirks of California’s vast political geography.
snippet: The candidates must know the quirks of California’s vast political geography.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Welcome, Democrats and debate spinners, to the city with a Mexican-American-Jewish-Italian Rhodes Scholar mayor, who is not running for president, in the state with an Irish Catholic governor who surely is, just not this time.

abstract: A letter from three former Fox News employees is designed to pressure presidential campaigns to do away with NDAs, calling them “a driving force in silencing workers.”
snippet: A letter from three former Fox News employees is designed to pressure presidential campaigns to do away with NDAs, calling them “a driving force in silencing workers.”
lead_paragraph: A new group founded by three former Fox News employees sent a letter to all presidential campaigns on Wednesday asking them to publicly condemn nondisclosure agreements that deal with workplace environment issues.
